---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Quvii — Independent Home Security Camera Reviews"
  description="Quvii is an independent home security camera review publication based in the United States. Honest, technical reviews of Ring, Eufy, Reolink, Blink, Arlo, Nest and more."
>
  <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-ink">About Quvii</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-body-faint">Independent. US-based. Reader-funded via affiliate links.</p>

  <div class="prose-pm max-w-prose">
    <p class="lead">
      Quvii is an independent publication covering home security cameras —
      reviews, buying guides, install tutorials, and the questions the
      manufacturers don't want you to ask.
    </p>

    <h2>What we cover</h2>
    <p>
      Wireless and PoE security cameras, video doorbells, floodlight cams,
      indoor monitors, baby/pet cameras, and the NVRs + software that tie
      them together. We focus on what a US shopper actually faces in 2026:
      Ring, Eufy, Reolink, Blink, Arlo, Nest, Wyze, Lorex, Amcrest, plus the
      enthusiast-grade Chinese brands (Hikvision, Dahua, Imou) that are
      increasingly mainstream in North America.
    </p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      Quvii is owned and operated by Quvii Inc., a US-headquartered company
      focused on home and small-business security. Our editorial team works
      independently from any equipment manufacturer or service provider —
      we take no payment for placement, no review-copy strings, and no
      embargoed-launch participation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Office address is in the process of being made public; until then,
      reach us at <strong>hello@quvii.com</strong> for editorial inquiries
      or <strong>corrections@quvii.com</strong> for fact-check requests.
    </p>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      Two ways, both disclosed:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Amazon Associates.</strong> When we recommend a camera in a
        comparison or buying guide, we link to it on Amazon. If you buy
        through that link, Amazon pays us a small percentage at no cost to
        you. Commission rates are the same across every product in a
        category, so we have zero financial incentive to favor Product A
        over Product B. See our
        <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Display advertising.</strong> Google AdSense on some content
        pages. Ads are not allowed to influence editorial — period. We use
        <code>ads.txt</code> + <code>sellers.json</code> compliant config so
        you can verify which networks we authorize.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do not currently accept paid placement, sponsored reviews, or
      "sponsored coverage" in any form. If a vendor offers us money in
      exchange for a review angle, we decline.
    </p>

    <h2>Our editorial process</h2>
    <p>
      The short version: every claim must trace to a source we'd be willing
      to defend in writing. The long version is documented in our
      <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a> — including how we
      use AI assistance, how we quality-gate articles before publishing, and
      our corrections process.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We don't run "best camera 2026" listicles that change every quarter just to chase clicks.</li>
      <li>We don't recommend products we wouldn't install in our own homes.</li>
      <li>We don't bury manufacturer issues — Ring's police-data partnerships, Eufy's 2022-2023 cloud-upload disclosures, and equivalent stories from other brands are covered honestly when they're relevant to a buying decision.</li>
      <li>We don't scrape, syndicate, or republish other reviewers' work without explicit credit + linkback.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Editorial / corrections: <strong>hello@quvii.com</strong></li>
      <li>Affiliate disclosure questions: <strong>hello@quvii.com</strong></li>
      <li>Press / partnership inquiries: <strong>hello@quvii.com</strong> (subject line: "Press")</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We respond within 3 business days. Material corrections get a
      "Corrected on YYYY-MM-DD" line published at the top of the affected
      article.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
